                        "displayName": "Dominic Luechinger",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Patch to solve the cookie problem",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=dol",
                        "name": "dol",
                        "displayName": "Dominic Luechinger",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2011-10-18T21:02:26.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2011-10-18T21:02:26.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/48974",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=adamlundrigan",
                        "name": "adamlundrigan",
                        "displayName": "Adam Lundrigan",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Yes, {{Zend_Http_CookieJar}} (and {{Zend_Http_Cookie}} as well) don't adhere exactly to the spec, but does it cause any real-world problems?\r\nI suspect that changing this behavior could qualify as a backwards-compatibility break (unlikely, IMHO).",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=adamlundrigan",
                        "name": "adamlundrigan",
                        "displayName": "Adam Lundrigan",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2011-11-03T16:21:08.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2011-11-03T16:21:08.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/48975",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=adamlundrigan",
                        "name": "adamlundrigan",
                        "displayName": "Adam Lundrigan",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Reproducing unit test:\r\n{code}\r\nIndex: tests\/Zend\/Http\/CookieJarTest.php\r\n===================================================================\r\n--- tests\/Zend\/Http\/CookieJarTest.php   (revision 24549)\r\n+++ tests\/Zend\/Http\/CookieJarTest.php   (working copy)\r\n@@ -470,4 +470,33 @@\r\n         $jar->reset();\r\n         $this->assertTrue($jar->isEmpty());\r\n     }\r\n+\r\n+    \/**\r\n+     * @group ZF-11726\r\n+     *\/\r\n+    public function testEnsureCookieJarWithSingleCookieAdheresToSyntaxSpecifiedInRfc6265()\r\n+    {\r\n+        $jar = new Zend_Http_CookieJar();\r\n+        $jar->addCookie(Zend_Http_Cookie::fromString('foo1=bar1; domain=.example.com; path=\/a\/b'));\r\n+\r\n+        $cookies = $jar->getAllCookies(Zend_Http_CookieJar::COOKIE_STRING_CONCAT);\r\n+        \/\/ Assert that last key-value pair does not end with separator (;)\r\n+        $this->assertNotRegExp('\/;$\/',ltrim($cookies));\r\n+    }\r\n+\r\n+    \/**\r\n+     * @group ZF-11726\r\n+     *\/\r\n+    public function testEnsureCookieJarWithMultipleCookiesAdheresToSyntaxSpecifiedInRfc6265()\r\n+    {\r\n+        $jar = new Zend_Http_CookieJar();\r\n+        $jar->addCookie(Zend_Http_Cookie::fromString('foo1=bar1; domain=.example.com; path=\/a\/b'));\r\n+        $jar->addCookie(Zend_Http_Cookie::fromString('foo2=bar2; domain=.example.com; path=\/c\/d'));\r\n+\r\n+        $cookies = $jar->getAllCookies(Zend_Http_CookieJar::COOKIE_STRING_CONCAT);\r\n+        \/\/ Assert that parts have a space right after the separator (;)\r\n+        $this->assertRegExp('\/^[^=]+=[^;]+; [^=]+=[^;]+$\/',ltrim($cookies));\r\n+        \/\/ Assert that last key-value pair does not end with separator (;)\r\n+        $this->assertNotRegExp('\/;$\/',ltrim($cookies));\r\n+    }\r\n }\r\n{code}",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=adamlundrigan",
                        "name": "adamlundrigan",
                        "displayName": "Adam Lundrigan",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2011-11-03T16:33:54.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2011-11-03T16:33:54.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/49013",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=dol",
                        "name": "dol",
                        "displayName": "Dominic Luechinger",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Dear Adam\r\n\r\nI had problem with a cPanel Server, with only allows RFC conform cookies. This harmed my application to fail and took me hours to figure out what caused the problem. I wasn't thinking a missing space makes the difference. Because I was such annoyed, I wrote this patch to avoid frustration in the future.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=dol",
                        "name": "dol",
                        "displayName": "Dominic Luechinger",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2011-11-07T23:31:30.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2011-11-07T23:31:30.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/49014",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=adamlundrigan",
                        "name": "adamlundrigan",
                        "displayName": "Adam Lundrigan",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Dominic:  Thank you for your feedback.  I'm not entirely certain it's possible to directly alter the current behavior of {{Zend_Http_CookieJar}}, as there may be implementations which rely on the current (albeit non-standard) behavior.  One thing we can investigate, though, is adding a \"strict\" mode so that the default behavior remains intact but one can switch on strict RFC6265 compatibility if necessary.  ",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=adamlundrigan",
                        "name": "adamlundrigan",
                        "displayName": "Adam Lundrigan",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2011-11-08T01:16:34.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2011-11-08T01:16:58.000+0000"
                },
